title: Zlatan Ibrahimovic has scored 14 goals against St Etienne | Daily Mail Online
text: 9 - Nantes, Lyon, Toulouse 8 - Fiorentina, Lorient 35-year-old Ibrahimovic has enjoyed a storied that has seen him play for Malmo, Ajax, Juventus, Inter Milan, Barcelona, Milan, PSG and now United. And of the many teams the Swedish striker has come up against, it's Saint-Etienne that have suffered most harshly. Ibrahimovic scored a hat-trick against them during PSG's 5-0 home league victory during the 2014-15 campaign, before returning to smash in three more when they met in the semi-finals of the French Cup later that season. Other clubs Zlatan has enjoyed playing against down the year include Palermo (12 goals), Marseille (11), Nice (11), Bastia (10), Parma (10) and Roma (10). Moving to United and the English Premier League has certainly not dulled his attacking instinct, with 20 goals in his 34 appearances so far this season. The Swedish striker trains at Carrington ahead of the first leg of United's last-32 fixture Jose Mourinho's team face a crucial run of fixtures in a number of competitions Man United next six
